00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,452
Is it supposed to be done this openly?

498
00:22:18,587 --> 00:22:20,505
There was nothing in it.

499
00:22:22,632 --> 00:22:23,467
Yeah.

500
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:26,136
More than anything, I felt sad.

501
00:22:26,219 --> 00:22:28,055
<i>I shouldn't have looked,</i>

502
00:22:28,138 --> 00:22:31,141
<i>but when we were all checking,</i>

503
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:35,145
I saw Do-geon's arm moving
to check how many he got.

504
00:22:35,228 --> 00:22:38,690
DO-GEON'S ARM MOVED AROUND BUSILY

505
00:22:38,774 --> 00:22:40,233
<i>While I had none.</i>

506
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:43,695
He didn't put in any either.
Why's he disappointed?

507
00:22:43,779 --> 00:22:45,113
You get what you give.

508
00:22:51,953 --> 00:22:55,332
<i>There were two notes</i>
<i>and Heart Chips inside.</i>

509
00:22:55,415 --> 00:22:57,375
CHAE-RIN → DO-GEON
5 HEARTS

510
00:22:57,459 --> 00:22:59,544
I HAD FUN TODAY
LET'S TALK MORE

511
00:22:59,628 --> 00:23:02,339
I gave five hearts to Do-geon

512
00:23:02,422 --> 00:23:04,674
because I was mostly drawn to him today.

513
00:23:04,758 --> 00:23:06,426
Was that too little? I don't know.

514
00:23:07,260 --> 00:23:09,638
GA-YEON → DO-GEON
7 HEARTS

515
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:11,556
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU!

516
00:23:12,432 --> 00:23:17,229
I decided to vote for the person
who seemed genuine and decent.

517
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:20,565
I think Chae-rin's were the yellow ones.

518
00:23:20,649 --> 00:23:25,153
We talked a lot
and I'm hoping they were from her too.

519
00:23:25,237 --> 00:23:27,197
<i>When I saw the Heart Chips,</i>

520
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:31,618
<i>I realized that I should have</i>
<i>put in this many</i>

521
00:23:31,701 --> 00:23:34,037
<i>to show how I feel.</i>

522
00:23:34,121 --> 00:23:35,163
PARK DO-GEON'S BOX

523
00:23:35,247 --> 00:23:36,540
CHAE-RIN: 5
GA-YEON: 7

524
00:23:45,090 --> 00:23:48,635
<i>To my surprise,</i>
<i>I ended up getting more than I expected.</i>

525
00:23:49,553 --> 00:23:51,555
<i>It looked like two people voted for me.</i>

526
00:23:57,644 --> 00:23:59,688
YOU'RE FUN
YE-RIM → KYUNG-HO: 11

527
00:23:59,771 --> 00:24:01,565
We kept teasing each other.

528
00:24:01,648 --> 00:24:06,236
<i>I made an effort to respond</i>
<i>to his teasing in a playful way.</i>

529
00:24:06,945 --> 00:24:07,904
There are potato chips.

530
00:24:07,988 --> 00:24:09,406
Melt it in a heart shape.

531
00:24:09,489 --> 00:24:11,116
With the potato chip?

532
00:24:11,908 --> 00:24:13,743
There was a window in front of us,

533
00:24:13,827 --> 00:24:14,911
<i>so I could see him.</i>

534
00:24:15,412 --> 00:24:16,538
We don't have time.

535
00:24:17,998 --> 00:24:19,916
-He's way too close to her.
-I know.

536
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,960
He might as well
put his arm on her shoulder.

537
00:24:22,919 --> 00:24:24,796
<i>He was very close to me.</i>

538
00:24:28,925 --> 00:24:31,803
<i>Maybe all that playful quipping</i>

539
00:24:33,013 --> 00:24:34,806
<i>made him end up sitting closer to me.</i>

540
00:24:34,890 --> 00:24:36,808
But this could all be in my head.

541
00:24:42,689 --> 00:24:46,067
<i>I voted for Kyung-ho.</i>

542
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:49,696
<i>I was simply thinking that</i>
<i>I should vote for the person I'm drawn to,</i>

543
00:24:50,238 --> 00:24:52,115
so I gave him this much.

544
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:55,785
YOU ARE SO FUNNY
HYE-WON → KYUNG-HO: 23

545
00:24:55,869 --> 00:24:57,287
KANG KYUNG-HO'S BOX

546
00:24:57,370 --> 00:24:59,122
YE-RIM: 11
HYE-WON: 23

547
00:24:59,206 --> 00:25:00,707
<i>It felt good.</i>

548
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:05,045
<i>I think I was hoping they were</i>
<i>from Ye-rim and Ga-yeon.</i>

549
00:25:05,128 --> 00:25:08,048
I could get the same color
or those colors could go elsewhere.

550
00:25:08,131 --> 00:25:10,675
Well, it was glorious,

551
00:25:10,759 --> 00:25:11,843
though it was for a moment.

552
00:25:11,927 --> 00:25:14,763
<i>All the boxes have been checked.</i>

553
00:25:18,016 --> 00:25:20,185
<i>I think I'm going to pass out tonight.</i>

554
00:25:20,685 --> 00:25:22,812
I'm going to bed when I get sleepy.

555
00:25:23,855 --> 00:25:25,565
What if you have fun without me?

556
00:25:26,149 --> 00:25:27,150
Is everyone here?

557
00:25:27,901 --> 00:25:29,277
-Oh, my gosh.
-Oh, my gosh.

558
00:25:29,361 --> 00:25:32,322
<i>You've been invited</i>
<i>to the King of Hearts game.</i>

559
00:25:32,405 --> 00:25:34,366
-I'm so scared.
-What?

560
00:25:34,449 --> 00:25:37,410
<i>Welcome to the King of Hearts game.</i>

561
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,121
King of Hearts game?

562
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:41,790
King of Hearts game?

563
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:42,707
King's Game?

564
00:25:42,791 --> 00:25:44,459
<i>We're playing the King's Game?</i>

565
00:25:44,542 --> 00:25:46,711
<i>Is it the King's Game that I know?</i>

566
00:25:47,295 --> 00:25:48,880
<i>I was a bit scared at first.</i>

567
00:25:48,964 --> 00:25:50,924
<i>My heart was racing.</i>

568
00:25:51,007 --> 00:25:52,634
Man, is it going to be like <i>Squid Game</i>?

569
00:25:52,717 --> 00:25:53,635
Nice to meet you.

570
00:25:53,718 --> 00:25:56,388
<i>From the moment</i>
<i>the subjects met for the first time,</i>

571
00:25:56,930 --> 00:25:59,057
<i>the King of Hearts game began.</i>

572
00:25:59,140 --> 00:26:01,393
<i>In this place where love becomes power,</i>

573
00:26:01,476 --> 00:26:04,145
<i>the feelings of the subjects</i>
<i>conveyed through Heart Chips</i>

574
00:26:04,229 --> 00:26:05,981
<i>will decide the king each day.</i>

575
00:26:07,399 --> 00:26:10,610
<i>The person with the most Heart Chips</i>
<i>for the day will become king.</i>

576
00:26:10,694 --> 00:26:11,778
HEART ROOM

577
00:26:11,861 --> 00:26:15,865
<i>They will be given immense power</i>
<i>that could change the romantic dynamics.</i>

578
00:26:15,949 --> 00:26:17,575
<i>The king will change every day</i>

579
00:26:17,659 --> 00:26:20,036
<i>and the king's privileges</i>
<i>will change every day as well.</i>

580
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:21,788
Anyway, it's a game.

581
00:26:23,373 --> 00:26:25,875
I only want to play the Penguin Game.

582
00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:33,758
<i>Moments ago, your Heart Chip votes</i>

583
00:26:33,842 --> 00:26:36,594
<i>created the very first king.</i>

584
00:26:36,678 --> 00:26:39,139
<i>Please congratulate him</i>
<i>with a round of applause.</i>

585
00:26:39,222 --> 00:26:41,266
PLEASE CONGRATULATE HIM
WITH A ROUND OF APPLAUSE

586
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:48,023
It looks fun. I want to play too.

587
00:26:50,442 --> 00:26:52,527
The king is decided?

588
00:26:52,610 --> 00:26:53,653
<i>The first king is…</i>

589
00:26:55,947 --> 00:26:58,158
This really is like <i>Squid Game.</i>

590
00:26:58,241 --> 00:27:00,952
They're giving the orders
along with classical music.

591
00:27:01,036 --> 00:27:03,455
Since it's 4 nights and 5 days,
they'll have 5 kings, right?

592
00:27:03,538 --> 00:27:04,664
No, none on the last day.

593
00:27:04,748 --> 00:27:05,999
-Four days.
-So four kings.

594
00:27:06,082 --> 00:27:08,418
We get to see the first king
to the fourth king.

595
00:27:08,501 --> 00:27:10,670
-Some might serve consecutive terms.
-Of course.

596
00:27:12,088 --> 00:27:13,465
<i>The first king is</i>

597
00:27:13,548 --> 00:27:14,758
<i>Kang Kyung-ho.</i>

598
00:27:14,841 --> 00:27:16,718
<i>It's Kang Kyung-ho.</i>

599
00:27:16,801 --> 00:27:18,595
1ST KING
KANG KYUNG-HO

600
00:27:19,179 --> 00:27:20,430
Kneel before me.

601
00:27:21,723 --> 00:27:22,807
Kneel.

602
00:27:22,891 --> 00:27:25,477
<i>The person who received</i>
<i>the most Heart Chips for the day</i>

603
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:26,895
<i>-will become king.</i>
-This is embarrassing.

604
00:27:27,771 --> 00:27:28,646
-Oh.
-Really?

605
00:27:28,730 --> 00:27:34,444
<i>Kyung-ho's kingship stays intact</i>
<i>until the Heart Chip vote tomorrow.</i>

606
00:27:36,196 --> 00:27:37,614
What the heck is going on?

607
00:27:37,697 --> 00:27:40,658
<i>The king's privilege</i>
<i>will be announced later.</i>

608
00:27:41,409 --> 00:27:42,285
Thank you.

609
00:27:42,369 --> 00:27:43,620
Interesting.

610
00:27:43,703 --> 00:27:45,330
I wonder what the privileges are.

611
00:27:45,413 --> 00:27:47,624
-What could it be?
-I know. I'm really curious.

612
00:27:47,707 --> 00:27:48,958
How do you feel, Your Majesty?

613
00:27:49,042 --> 00:27:49,876
-Me?
-Speech.

614
00:27:49,959 --> 00:27:51,086
-Give us a speech.
-Speech.

615
00:27:51,169 --> 00:27:53,046
I feel like I've broken down.

616
00:27:54,297 --> 00:27:56,424
<i>Honestly, I didn't know how to react.</i>

617
00:27:56,508 --> 00:27:57,342
You see,

618
00:27:58,301 --> 00:27:59,511
it was so awkward.

619
00:27:59,594 --> 00:28:01,638
You're the king of this kingdom.

620
00:28:01,721 --> 00:28:02,555
Kingdom?

621
00:28:03,556 --> 00:28:04,432
<i>I felt proud.</i>

622
00:28:04,516 --> 00:28:06,976
I put you on that throne.

623
00:28:11,856 --> 00:28:14,025
Hye-won, I love your self-esteem.

624
00:28:14,109 --> 00:28:16,319
She was like a royal consort
who gave birth to a son.

625
00:28:18,446 --> 00:28:20,657
-You know, the son--
-"I put you on that throne."

626
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:22,992
-"I got you where you are."
-"I put you there."

627
00:28:23,076 --> 00:28:25,537
I put you on that throne.

628
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:27,497
I appoint you as king.

629
00:28:27,580 --> 00:28:30,417
<i>I really put a lot in your box,</i>

630
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:32,419
<i>so I practically made you king.</i>

631
00:28:32,919 --> 00:28:34,587
<i>"You're happy right now, aren't you?"</i>

632
00:28:34,671 --> 00:28:35,880
<i>"That's all thanks to me."</i>

633
00:28:35,964 --> 00:28:37,215
<i>That's how I felt.</i>

634
00:28:37,298 --> 00:28:39,259
<i>I was wondering if it was me</i>

635
00:28:39,342 --> 00:28:41,553
or if it was because
someone else put theirs in.

636
00:28:41,636 --> 00:28:42,470
I wondered.

637
00:28:42,554 --> 00:28:44,264
DO-GEON: CHAE-RIN 5, GA-YEON 7
KYUNG-HO: HYE-WON 23, YE-RIM 11

638
00:28:44,347 --> 00:28:47,058
JUNG-MIN: 0, DO-GEON: 12, KYUNG-HO: 34

639
00:28:47,142 --> 00:28:50,353
<i>The person who I thought would be popular</i>
<i>ended up being popular.</i>

640
00:28:50,437 --> 00:28:53,565
<i>Did all the other women</i>
<i>besides me vote for Kyung-ho?</i>

641
00:28:53,648 --> 00:28:55,775
I should've put more in Do-geon's box.

642
00:28:55,859 --> 00:28:58,403
It's not like I got a small amount,

643
00:28:58,486 --> 00:29:01,239
<i>so I wondered how many votes Kyung-ho got.</i>

644
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:05,618
<i>I guess Kyung-ho is the most popular.</i>

645
00:29:05,702 --> 00:29:07,620
He's very attractive,

646
00:29:07,704 --> 00:29:09,205
so my eyes keep drifting toward him.

647
00:29:09,289 --> 00:29:11,291
<i>Without even realizing it,</i>

648
00:29:11,374 --> 00:29:13,042
<i>my gaze would often shift to him.</i>

649
00:29:13,668 --> 00:29:14,794
You can just relax.

650
00:29:15,378 --> 00:29:16,296
Okay.

651
00:29:16,379 --> 00:29:17,380
No one…

652
00:29:20,717 --> 00:29:23,428
-I think Ga-yeon likes Kyung-ho too.
-Yeah.

653
00:29:23,511 --> 00:29:25,180
-Yeah.
-I think it's Kyung-ho too.

654
00:29:27,932 --> 00:29:29,809
<i>We should check the mailbox.</i>

655
00:29:29,893 --> 00:29:31,227
Should the king be going?

656
00:29:31,311 --> 00:29:32,937
You shouldn't be moving, Your Majesty.

657
00:29:33,021 --> 00:29:34,647
I should lead by example.

658
00:29:34,731 --> 00:29:36,107
Maybe they'll let us know now.

659
00:29:36,191 --> 00:29:37,484
-His power?
-Yeah.

660
00:29:37,567 --> 00:29:39,068
-I wonder what his powers are.
-I think so.

661
00:29:40,987 --> 00:29:42,030
Read it to us now.

662
00:29:42,113 --> 00:29:44,115
I'll read it, Your Majesty.

663
00:29:44,199 --> 00:29:45,366
Okay.

664
00:29:45,450 --> 00:29:47,368
-It really suits her.
-I know.

665
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:48,995
"The male tenants

666
00:29:49,078 --> 00:29:51,748
must sit next to the woman
they want to go on a date with,

667
00:29:51,831 --> 00:29:52,665
hold their hand…

668
00:29:56,169 --> 00:29:57,962
and ask her out on a date."

669
00:29:58,046 --> 00:29:59,756
Why do they like holding hands so much?

670
00:30:00,423 --> 00:30:01,549
Holding hands is the start.

671
00:30:01,633 --> 00:30:03,718
-That's how <i>The Love Lab</i> starts.
-Why?

672
00:30:03,802 --> 00:30:05,386
They're obsessed with holding hands.

673
00:30:05,470 --> 00:30:07,472
Let's just have them hold hands
at the start next time.

674
00:30:07,555 --> 00:30:09,766
"After everyone has
asked someone out on a date,

675
00:30:09,849 --> 00:30:11,684
the final date will be decided."

676
00:30:13,353 --> 00:30:14,646
Now?

677
00:30:14,729 --> 00:30:15,563
Right now?

678
00:30:16,731 --> 00:30:18,525
-Please wait.
-Hang on.

679
00:30:18,608 --> 00:30:20,777
I thought it made no sense.

680
00:30:20,860 --> 00:30:23,029
What are we supposed to do
while we wait?

681
00:30:23,112 --> 00:30:25,615
But one woman will be left out.

682
00:30:25,698 --> 00:30:27,617
Then you go on a date with your bed.

683
00:30:28,201 --> 00:30:31,246
<i>Since I didn't get any votes</i>
<i>in the first-impression round…</i>

684
00:30:31,329 --> 00:30:34,833
<i>I wasn't going to get my hopes up</i>
<i>and just practice mind control.</i>

685
00:30:34,916 --> 00:30:36,417
What about the order?

686
00:30:36,501 --> 00:30:37,794
What do you think, Your Majesty?

687
00:30:38,545 --> 00:30:41,089
<i>I wanted to go on a date with Kyung-ho,</i>

688
00:30:41,589 --> 00:30:44,133
but I had no clue
who he was going to choose.

689
00:30:44,217 --> 00:30:46,553
But he decided to go first.

690
00:30:46,636 --> 00:30:48,263
I don't know. I'll just go first.

691
00:30:49,264 --> 00:30:51,349
<i>I was really scared</i>

692
00:30:51,432 --> 00:30:53,560
<i>that I wouldn't get chosen.</i>

693
00:30:53,643 --> 00:30:54,811
Number two and three?

694
00:30:55,353 --> 00:30:56,271
SECOND

695
00:30:56,354 --> 00:30:57,480
THIRD

696
00:30:59,107 --> 00:31:00,984
-We feel so shy right now.
-What? Right.

697
00:31:01,568 --> 00:31:03,027
THE WOMEN LEAVE THE SEAT BESIDE THEM OPEN

698
00:31:03,903 --> 00:31:05,572
KYUNG-HO IS UP

699
00:31:08,324 --> 00:31:09,868
<i>Even so,</i>

700
00:31:09,951 --> 00:31:11,327
<i>a part of me did have expectations.</i>

701
00:31:11,411 --> 00:31:13,371
<i>If Kyung-ho chose someone else,</i>

702
00:31:13,454 --> 00:31:16,124
<i>I'd feel weird about that as well.</i>

703
00:31:17,792 --> 00:31:19,878
<i>I wanted to run away.</i>

704
00:31:49,365 --> 00:31:50,950
Let's go on a date tomorrow.

705
00:31:51,534 --> 00:31:52,368
Shall we?

706
00:31:53,036 --> 00:31:53,912
Can you

707
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:56,039
make it sound less cocky?

708
00:31:56,122 --> 00:31:56,956
-Me?
-Yes.

709
00:31:59,542 --> 00:32:01,753
Please go on a date with me tomorrow.

710
00:32:01,836 --> 00:32:02,795
Okay.

711
00:32:06,215 --> 00:32:08,134
-I'll go on a date with you.
-Okay.

712
00:32:08,217 --> 00:32:09,594
<i>I was really surprised</i>

713
00:32:10,178 --> 00:32:11,179
and relieved.

714
00:32:11,262 --> 00:32:14,015
The way he stuttered was
the ultimate cuteness.

715
00:32:15,558 --> 00:32:17,518
<i>My hand was shaking</i>

716
00:32:18,144 --> 00:32:20,188
<i>and my voice was shaking too.</i>

717
00:32:20,271 --> 00:32:22,315
I was so nervous that
I couldn't look at her.

718
00:32:22,398 --> 00:32:23,816
How long do we hold hands?

719
00:32:23,900 --> 00:32:25,151
You can let go.

720
00:32:27,278 --> 00:32:28,446
He let go immediately.

721
00:32:28,529 --> 00:32:32,200
He chose me in front of everybody.

722
00:32:32,283 --> 00:32:33,534
That was brave of him.

723
00:32:36,537 --> 00:32:38,373
THE NEXT PARTICIPANT IS NERVOUS

724
00:32:38,957 --> 00:32:41,876
<i>I was worried</i>
<i>because no one voted for me.</i>

725
00:32:42,752 --> 00:32:44,879
<i>What if she doesn't like it</i>
<i>when I hold her hand?</i>

726
00:32:46,005 --> 00:32:48,549
I'd feel so awkward and embarrassed.

727
00:32:49,592 --> 00:32:54,889
<i>I kind of expected Kyung-ho</i>
<i>to hold Ye-rim's hand.</i>

728
00:32:55,473 --> 00:32:56,849
<i>And I thought</i>

729
00:32:57,433 --> 00:33:00,478
<i>Jung-min might hold Chae-rin's hand.</i>

730
00:33:06,317 --> 00:33:08,361
KYUNG-HO VACATES THE SEAT NEXT TO YE-RIM

731
00:33:14,993 --> 00:33:15,952
Would you…

732
00:33:18,621 --> 00:33:21,207
Would you go on a date with me tomorrow?

733
00:33:21,290 --> 00:33:22,208
I'd love that.

734
00:33:24,711 --> 00:33:27,130
DATE SELECTION
JUNG-MIN → GA-YEON

735
00:33:29,007 --> 00:33:29,966
He's so happy.

736
00:33:30,049 --> 00:33:31,175
Jung-min is so happy.

737
00:33:31,259 --> 00:33:33,845
Ga-yeon said yes immediately though.

738
00:33:42,061 --> 00:33:45,148
I really thought
my heart was going to burst.

739
00:33:46,858 --> 00:33:48,609
<i>His hand was very big.</i>

740
00:33:48,693 --> 00:33:49,694
I'm wide awake now.

741
00:33:54,032 --> 00:33:55,199
<i>It made my heart flutter.</i>

742
00:33:58,745 --> 00:34:01,789
<i>My heart skipped a beat</i>
<i>while I was holding her hand.</i>

743
00:34:01,873 --> 00:34:04,125
<i>But I kept holding her hand tightly.</i>

744
00:34:05,626 --> 00:34:07,837
She didn't try to pull away,

745
00:34:07,920 --> 00:34:09,964
so I took that as a good sign.

746
00:34:14,844 --> 00:34:16,721
<i>I didn't get any first-impression votes,</i>

747
00:34:16,804 --> 00:34:20,141
<i>so I was really curious as to</i>
<i>why he asked me out on a date.</i>

748
00:34:23,436 --> 00:34:25,855
He did a good job targeting someone
who isn't popular.

749
00:34:25,938 --> 00:34:29,025
But Ga-yeon put her Heart Chips
in Do-geon's box, right?

750
00:34:29,108 --> 00:34:32,111
She put her chips in Do-geon's,
but she keeps gazing at Kyung-ho.

751
00:34:32,195 --> 00:34:33,738
Jung-min wasn't even on her radar.

752
00:34:33,821 --> 00:34:36,115
But he was the one
who chose her when she was sad

753
00:34:36,199 --> 00:34:37,658
-about getting zero votes.
-Right.

754
00:34:37,742 --> 00:34:38,868
She's thankful.

755
00:34:39,452 --> 00:34:41,370
LAST ONE UP

756
00:34:41,454 --> 00:34:44,457
<i>I was hoping for Do-geon to come.</i>

757
00:34:50,963 --> 00:34:54,217
<i>You never know.</i>
<i>He might hold Ye-rim's hand.</i>

758
00:35:03,267 --> 00:35:05,728
They interlocked their fingers!

759
00:35:06,729 --> 00:35:07,605
Wait.

760
00:35:07,688 --> 00:35:09,649
-Isn't that kind of exciting too?
-What is?

761
00:35:09,732 --> 00:35:11,984
He didn't grab her hand
but let her put her hand on his.

762
00:35:12,610 --> 00:35:14,278
"I'll interlock my fingers."

763
00:35:16,531 --> 00:35:19,117
-Do-geon spread out his fingers, right?
-Yeah.

764
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:20,451
He meant for her to do that.

765
00:35:20,535 --> 00:35:21,744
-Interlock them.
-Let's watch.

766
00:35:22,578 --> 00:35:24,038
Wait, no!

767
00:35:24,122 --> 00:35:25,498
He didn't do that.

768
00:35:25,581 --> 00:35:27,166
He didn't intend her to do that.

769
00:35:27,250 --> 00:35:29,043
-It was just, "Put it on mine."
-Right.

770
00:35:29,127 --> 00:35:30,795
-But she interlocked them.
-Yes, she did that.

771
00:35:30,878 --> 00:35:32,088
Like a trap.

772
00:35:32,171 --> 00:35:33,005
Yeah, she's saying,

773
00:35:33,589 --> 00:35:35,466
-"I'm going to hold you tight."
-Yeah.

774
00:35:40,930 --> 00:35:42,598
Will you go on a date with me tomorrow?

775
00:35:42,682 --> 00:35:43,933
DATE SELECTION
DO-GEON → CHAE-RIN

776
00:35:44,016 --> 00:35:44,851
Yes.

777
00:35:47,728 --> 00:35:48,771
Is this right?

778
00:35:50,022 --> 00:35:51,149
<i>It felt moist.</i>

779
00:35:51,232 --> 00:35:52,275
<i>It was sweaty.</i>

780
00:35:53,109 --> 00:35:55,528
I could tell that he was nervous.

781
00:35:55,611 --> 00:35:56,445
That was cute.

782
00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:04,579
-This is so hard.
-I'll watch the house, then.

783
00:36:06,747 --> 00:36:10,042
<i>I don't know. I don't even remember.</i>
<i>I was so embarrassed.</i>

784
00:36:10,126 --> 00:36:13,337
It wasn't about not being chosen
or not holding hands.

785
00:36:13,421 --> 00:36:16,132
I just didn't want to be alone.

786
00:36:16,215 --> 00:36:17,925
<i>What am I going to do tomorrow?</i>

787
00:36:18,009 --> 00:36:19,802
<i>I came all the way here,</i>

788
00:36:19,886 --> 00:36:23,514
<i>so I was so sad</i>
<i>that I had to spend time alone.</i>

789
00:36:23,598 --> 00:36:25,057
<i>That's what made me sad.</i>

790
00:36:25,141 --> 00:36:26,475
<i>That's what upset me the most.</i>

791
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:29,353
Are you okay?

792
00:36:30,188 --> 00:36:31,022
Right now?

793
00:36:31,522 --> 00:36:34,108
I haven't covered my face
with makeup in so long.

794
00:36:34,192 --> 00:36:35,276
Do you usually wear makeup?

795
00:36:35,359 --> 00:36:36,736
-No.
-Almost never?

796
00:36:36,819 --> 00:36:37,653
What about tomorrow?

797
00:36:38,654 --> 00:36:40,698
I'll have to since I'm here.

798
00:36:40,781 --> 00:36:43,242
What if you end up
with theatrical makeup tomorrow?

799
00:36:43,326 --> 00:36:45,286
-Help me out, please.
-I'll help you out.

800
00:36:45,369 --> 00:36:46,829
-I don't know how to wear makeup.
-Really?

801
00:36:46,913 --> 00:36:47,788
Help you with what?

802
00:36:47,872 --> 00:36:48,915
-Makeup.
-With the makeup.

803
00:36:49,832 --> 00:36:51,209
Are you good at it? I bet you are.

804
00:36:51,292 --> 00:36:52,501
I'm unsure about one thing.

805
00:36:52,585 --> 00:36:53,669
Are you good at contouring?

806
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:56,839
-Can you help me with contouring?
-Okay.

807
00:36:56,923 --> 00:36:58,507
His eyebrows are so pretty.

808
00:36:58,591 --> 00:37:00,009
Who?

809
00:37:00,092 --> 00:37:02,345
-His eyebrows.
-His eyebrows? Yeah, they're very pretty.

810
00:37:03,346 --> 00:37:05,556
The makeup artist did her best today.

811
00:37:06,224 --> 00:37:07,725
-It's really pretty.
-Is it?

812
00:37:11,145 --> 00:37:12,730
He can't look her in the eye!

813
00:37:14,690 --> 00:37:16,943
-That's usually what the man does.
-Yeah.

814
00:37:17,026 --> 00:37:18,945
-But--
-But Chae-rin already trapped him.

815
00:37:19,028 --> 00:37:20,404
-Yeah.
-She trapped him already.

816
00:37:20,488 --> 00:37:21,989
He's hers now.

817
00:37:22,073 --> 00:37:25,159
-She's more proactive than I expected.
-Yeah.

818
00:37:25,826 --> 00:37:27,328
-It's really pretty.
-Is it?

819
00:37:29,247 --> 00:37:31,791
I don't think I have that shade.
What should I do?

820
00:37:31,874 --> 00:37:34,877
Why did King Kyung-ho choose her?

821
00:37:34,961 --> 00:37:35,836
Oh, my.

822
00:37:37,171 --> 00:37:38,214
-Me?
-Yes.

823
00:37:39,924 --> 00:37:40,967
How nerve-racking.

824
00:37:42,593 --> 00:37:43,761
Because she's pretty.

825
00:37:45,263 --> 00:37:47,181
You like her looks the most.

826
00:37:47,932 --> 00:37:49,100
Let's stop here.

827
00:37:51,227 --> 00:37:53,562
Can't we hear more?

828
00:37:54,146 --> 00:37:55,231
Then,

829
00:37:55,314 --> 00:37:56,983
why did you choose her?

830
00:37:59,860 --> 00:38:00,903
Beside her looks.

831
00:38:00,987 --> 00:38:02,029
Beside her looks?

832
00:38:03,489 --> 00:38:04,824
Because the baby hairs look cute.

833
00:38:05,533 --> 00:38:06,492
Something like that.

834
00:38:07,535 --> 00:38:08,661
Or

835
00:38:08,744 --> 00:38:10,371
because she looks good
in that white cardigan.

836
00:38:12,206 --> 00:38:14,041
-He's a player.
-He's flirting.

837
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:16,752
He's telling them
what he finds attractive about her.

838
00:38:16,836 --> 00:38:17,753
He's flirting.

839
00:38:18,421 --> 00:38:20,047
…because she looks good
in that white cardigan.

840
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:28,472
<i>I may act like I'm rooting</i>
<i>for Ga-yeon and Jung-min,</i>

841
00:38:28,556 --> 00:38:31,267
but I'm also very curious about Ga-yeon.

842
00:38:31,350 --> 00:38:33,769
But since I chose Ye-rim,

843
00:38:33,853 --> 00:38:35,938
that's a different matter.

844
00:38:36,022 --> 00:38:38,482
Up until this point,

845
00:38:38,566 --> 00:38:40,901
she is the person who I am

846
00:38:41,819 --> 00:38:42,862
most curious about.

847
00:38:44,405 --> 00:38:46,157
That's a good answer. You're curious.

848
00:38:48,743 --> 00:38:49,577
…most curious about.

849
00:38:53,414 --> 00:38:55,499
<i>Now, the king's privilege…</i>

850
00:38:56,083 --> 00:38:58,669
<i>The king's privilege will be announced.</i>

851
00:39:00,546 --> 00:39:03,841
<i>The first king</i>
<i>Kang Kyung-ho's privilege is…</i>

852
00:39:05,468 --> 00:39:07,011
<i>the power to decide the date.</i>

853
00:39:08,679 --> 00:39:10,765
<i>It's the power to decide the date.</i>

854
00:39:11,432 --> 00:39:14,435
<i>The number of people</i>
<i>who can go on tomorrow's date are</i>

855
00:39:14,518 --> 00:39:16,062
<i>only four of you.</i>

856
00:39:16,145 --> 00:39:18,731
<i>Regardless of</i>
<i>who was asked out on a date,</i>

857
00:39:18,814 --> 00:39:23,361
<i>the king may freely</i>
<i>mix and match the partners of the date.</i>

858
00:39:24,236 --> 00:39:25,154
What?

859
00:39:25,237 --> 00:39:27,114
-This is insane.
<i>-Tomorrow's date</i>

860
00:39:27,198 --> 00:39:29,992
<i>is solely in the hands of the king.</i>

861
00:39:35,039 --> 00:39:36,540
ONLY THE 4 CHOSEN BY THE KING

862
00:39:36,624 --> 00:39:38,209
