00:56:31,221 --> 00:56:32,680
I thought I was in a zoo.

1231
00:56:33,181 --> 00:56:34,224
When we open the tent,

1232
00:56:35,016 --> 00:56:36,351
there might be a lot of animals.

1233
00:56:36,434 --> 00:56:39,187
I'll go and get some warm water.

1234
00:56:43,233 --> 00:56:44,484
He's sound asleep.

1235
00:56:44,567 --> 00:56:46,319
The weather is so nice,

1236
00:56:46,402 --> 00:56:48,822
so I'm going to enjoy
the outdoors some more.

1237
00:56:48,905 --> 00:56:50,657
-Hye-won.
-Yes?

1238
00:56:50,740 --> 00:56:51,866
What is he like?

1239
00:56:51,950 --> 00:56:53,409
It's a secret.

1240
00:56:53,993 --> 00:56:55,203
FOR THE GUEST THAT ONLY SHE KNOWS

1241
00:56:55,995 --> 00:56:58,748
HYE-WON PREPARES SOMETHING

1242
00:56:59,332 --> 00:57:00,875
I brought some warm water.

1243
00:57:00,959 --> 00:57:02,127
Thank you.

1244
00:57:02,794 --> 00:57:04,337
It's a yin-yang drink.

1245
00:57:04,420 --> 00:57:06,297
-Mixing cold and hot water?
-Yeah.

1246
00:57:06,381 --> 00:57:08,466
You have to drink it in the morning.

1247
00:57:08,550 --> 00:57:10,635
It helps with digestion.

1248
00:57:10,718 --> 00:57:11,970
-It's so nice.
-Yeah.

1249
00:57:12,053 --> 00:57:14,597
From a science major's perspective,
it was just warm water.

1250
00:57:14,681 --> 00:57:17,434
It's not about whether
I believe in the yin yang philosophy.

1251
00:57:17,517 --> 00:57:20,311
I was just touched by the gesture.

1252
00:57:20,395 --> 00:57:22,230
<i>-See you later.</i>
<i>-See you later.</i>

1253
00:57:23,356 --> 00:57:25,483
<i>-Jung-min.</i>
<i>-Yes?</i>

1254
00:57:25,567 --> 00:57:26,901
-Here?
-Should we do it here?

1255
00:57:26,985 --> 00:57:28,319
-Close your eyes.
-Make it bold.

1256
00:57:31,865 --> 00:57:33,658
<i>Ga-yeon told me to close my eyes.</i>

1257
00:57:33,741 --> 00:57:36,661
<i>I wanted to look at her</i>
<i>and study her face.</i>

1258
00:57:40,165 --> 00:57:41,499
Make my nose sharp like a blade.

1259
00:57:43,918 --> 00:57:45,378
It's already pretty nicely shaped.

1260
00:57:46,754 --> 00:57:48,214
It's kind of round.

1261
00:57:49,966 --> 00:57:52,343
<i>It felt kind of strange.</i>

1262
00:57:52,427 --> 00:57:54,137
<i>My heart was fluttering and I was happy,</i>

1263
00:57:54,220 --> 00:57:56,347
<i>but I wondered if she felt the same way.</i>

1264
00:57:58,141 --> 00:57:58,975
I feel so at ease.

1265
00:58:04,105 --> 00:58:05,982
Let me do it for you, sir.

1266
00:58:06,065 --> 00:58:08,234
Do you have dry skin? You do.

1267
00:58:08,318 --> 00:58:10,111
Is this what you're wearing on our date?

1268
00:58:10,195 --> 00:58:12,197
Yes, what do you think?

1269
00:58:12,280 --> 00:58:13,239
You look pretty.

1270
00:58:14,699 --> 00:58:16,701
I woke up at seven o'clock.

1271
00:58:16,784 --> 00:58:18,328
-Why'd you wake up so early?
-Maybe 7:30.

1272
00:58:18,411 --> 00:58:19,621
My eyes just opened.

1273
00:58:20,246 --> 00:58:23,291
I was so hungry
that I had instant noodles.

1274
00:58:23,374 --> 00:58:24,709
You did? What kind?

1275
00:58:24,792 --> 00:58:25,793
Noodles with kimchi.

1276
00:58:27,253 --> 00:58:28,630
Did someone draw your eyebrows?

1277
00:58:28,713 --> 00:58:29,797
-Eyebrows--
-Go like this.

1278
00:58:31,758 --> 00:58:33,593
I asked you a question
but made you close your mouth.

1279
00:58:33,676 --> 00:58:35,345
I was about to say that.

1280
00:58:35,970 --> 00:58:37,430
You asked me a question but went, "Mm."

1281
00:58:39,474 --> 00:58:40,850
You aren't done dolling up?

1282
00:58:40,934 --> 00:58:42,185
No, I'm done.

1283
00:58:43,645 --> 00:58:45,355
-How do I look?
-You look pretty.

1284
00:58:45,438 --> 00:58:46,272
Yeah?

1285
00:58:48,483 --> 00:58:50,818
We really look like a couple
with our navy tops, don't we?

1286
00:58:52,153 --> 00:58:53,988
-How do you open this?
-They'll be surprised.

1287
00:58:54,572 --> 00:58:56,282
Wait, did you two match your outfits?

1288
00:58:56,366 --> 00:58:58,284
-What do you think?
-That's adorable.

1289
00:58:58,368 --> 00:58:59,869
Adorable? You mean, pretty.

1290
00:59:01,412 --> 00:59:02,664
It's cute.

1291
00:59:03,248 --> 00:59:05,166
What jacket are you going to wear?

1292
00:59:05,250 --> 00:59:06,334
-Me?
-Yeah.

1293
00:59:06,417 --> 00:59:08,836
You want to match
your outfits too, don't you?

1294
00:59:08,920 --> 00:59:11,047
-Yes.
-Yeah, you have to coordinate.

1295
00:59:11,130 --> 00:59:12,257
It'll be exciting that way.

1296
00:59:14,551 --> 00:59:15,969
You aren't going on a date though.

1297
00:59:16,052 --> 00:59:17,011
Yes, we are.

1298
00:59:17,720 --> 00:59:18,638
Because of someone…

1299
00:59:18,721 --> 00:59:20,431
-Because of a certain someone.
-Right?

1300
00:59:20,515 --> 00:59:22,433
-That tyrant.
-Tyrant…

1301
00:59:23,518 --> 00:59:24,519
<i>Let's eat.</i>

1302
00:59:30,358 --> 00:59:31,901
He looks so different.

1303
00:59:32,443 --> 00:59:34,445
-What? Because of the makeup?
-Is it magic?

1304
00:59:34,529 --> 00:59:36,573
-I worked my magic.
-It's magic.

1305
00:59:36,656 --> 00:59:38,408
He really looks different.

1306
00:59:38,491 --> 00:59:39,617
Do-geon.

1307
00:59:39,701 --> 00:59:41,411
Can you show us your face?

1308
00:59:41,494 --> 00:59:43,371
-Is he wearing makeup?
-She did it for him.

1309
00:59:43,454 --> 00:59:44,789
Everyone complimented me.

1310
00:59:44,872 --> 00:59:46,708
I did some contouring on him too.

1311
00:59:46,791 --> 00:59:48,501
-Yeah, how is it?
-Doesn't he look handsome?

1312
00:59:48,585 --> 00:59:50,837
-Yeah, he looks dapper.
-Yeah, for real.

1313
00:59:54,591 --> 00:59:55,592
That must be him.

1314
01:00:03,725 --> 01:00:04,809
Hello.

1315
01:00:05,393 --> 01:00:06,477
Hello.

1316
01:00:06,561 --> 01:00:07,437
Come in.

1317
01:00:08,396 --> 01:00:10,690
We got a letter.

1318
01:00:11,482 --> 01:00:12,567
It isn't a letter.

1319
01:00:13,359 --> 01:00:14,611
Come this way.

1320
01:00:15,612 --> 01:00:16,446
-Is he here?
-Yes.

1321
01:00:16,529 --> 01:00:18,656
-Hello.
-Hello.

1322
01:00:19,240 --> 01:00:20,617
Nice to meet you.

1323
01:00:20,700 --> 01:00:22,452
"Nice to meet you"?

1324
01:00:22,535 --> 01:00:24,495
THE FINAL SUBJECT ARRIVES AT THE LODGING

1325
01:00:25,538 --> 01:00:26,456
Hello.

1326
01:00:26,539 --> 01:00:30,501
<i>Naturally, the person I knew</i>
<i>caught my eye first.</i>

1327
01:00:31,002 --> 01:00:32,211
Did you get some sleep?

1328
01:00:32,295 --> 01:00:33,504
No.

1329
01:00:33,588 --> 01:00:35,715
-No sleep after you got back?
-No, I didn't get any.

1330
01:00:35,798 --> 01:00:38,301
Shouldn't we introduce ourselves?

1331
01:00:38,885 --> 01:00:40,678
Okay, please proceed.

1332
01:00:40,762 --> 01:00:42,639
-But you're the king.
-You're the king.

1333
01:00:44,182 --> 01:00:45,224
Why are you the king?

1334
01:00:46,893 --> 01:00:48,144
It's a secret.

1335
01:00:48,227 --> 01:00:49,354
Oh, you don't know.

1336
01:00:49,937 --> 01:00:51,147
I don't know anything.

1337
01:00:51,230 --> 01:00:52,106
You'll find out.

1338
01:00:52,607 --> 01:00:53,858
I'm Kang Kyung-ho.

1339
01:00:53,941 --> 01:00:55,485
Your name is Kang Kyung-ho.

1340
01:00:55,568 --> 01:00:57,570
-Yes, I'm the king.
-The king.

1341
01:00:58,905 --> 01:01:00,865
I don't know anything.

1342
01:01:00,948 --> 01:01:02,408
I don't know what it means to be king.

1343
01:01:02,492 --> 01:01:04,952
Is there anything you'd like to tell me?

1344
01:01:05,536 --> 01:01:06,537
We don't know that well either.

1345
01:01:06,621 --> 01:01:08,998
Should we tell him
about the one thing from yesterday?

1346
01:01:09,082 --> 01:01:09,957
Yesterday?

1347
01:01:10,041 --> 01:01:11,584
We played tug of war.

1348
01:01:11,668 --> 01:01:13,086
-Tug of war?
-Yes.

1349
01:01:13,169 --> 01:01:15,672
-That's how we decided the beds.
-We got our own food too.

1350
01:01:15,755 --> 01:01:16,923
We had pillow fights too.

1351
01:01:18,341 --> 01:01:19,509
We got injured.

1352
01:01:19,592 --> 01:01:21,010
Is it like a survival thing?

1353
01:01:21,803 --> 01:01:23,888
-We did a treasure hunt.
-A treasure hunt?

1354
01:01:26,182 --> 01:01:27,934
There must be a reason why he's king.

1355
01:01:29,435 --> 01:01:31,354
Do I have to be on his good side
since he's king?

1356
01:01:31,437 --> 01:01:33,523
-Yeah, you have to.
-I do, right?

1357
01:01:33,606 --> 01:01:35,817
Do you get an advantage
if you win the king's favor?

1358
01:01:36,609 --> 01:01:37,694
Yes.

1359
01:01:37,777 --> 01:01:38,736
Let's get along, sir.

1360
01:01:40,321 --> 01:01:41,739
You can become king today.

1361
01:01:41,823 --> 01:01:42,949
I'm getting that ambition.

1362
01:01:43,032 --> 01:01:44,784
-To be king.
-Whoa.

1363
01:01:46,869 --> 01:01:49,664
YE-RIM AND KYUNG-HO ARE OFF TO THEIR DATE

1364
01:01:49,747 --> 01:01:50,832
-Where do I go?
-Hop in.

1365
01:01:50,915 --> 01:01:51,749
Okay.

1366
01:01:52,291 --> 01:01:53,376
Thank you.

1367
01:02:01,801 --> 01:02:04,262
-Hello.
-Hello.

1368
01:02:05,221 --> 01:02:06,848
<i>Have you been around here before?</i>

1369
01:02:06,931 --> 01:02:08,891
<i>-This is Ganghwado, right?</i>
<i>-Yeah.</i>

1370
01:02:08,975 --> 01:02:10,935
I think I came here when I was little.

1371
01:02:14,814 --> 01:02:15,773
It won't come out.

1372
01:02:19,777 --> 01:02:21,446
-What is it?
-Bug.

1373
01:02:23,322 --> 01:02:24,407
All done.

1374
01:02:27,952 --> 01:02:29,746
YE-RIM AND KYUNG-HO
GANGHWA LUGE

1375
01:02:29,829 --> 01:02:30,663
<i>This looks fun.</i>

1376
01:02:31,164 --> 01:02:33,458
BOARDING THE CABLECAR

1377
01:02:33,541 --> 01:02:34,375
Oh, my.

1378
01:02:36,544 --> 01:02:39,005
THE LUGE BOARDING AREA
LOCATED AT THE MOUNTAIN SUMMIT

1379
01:02:40,965 --> 01:02:41,799
KYUNG-HO'S SELF-CAM

1380
01:02:41,883 --> 01:02:43,217
-Can I film you?
-Yes.

1381
01:02:43,301 --> 01:02:44,844
Do you prefer your right or left side?

1382
01:02:44,927 --> 01:02:46,304
It doesn't matter to me.

1383
01:02:47,638 --> 01:02:48,473
Look here.

1384
01:02:51,642 --> 01:02:52,643
-Fascinated?
-Yeah.

1385
01:02:52,727 --> 01:02:54,979
This is what you call "new technology."

1386
01:02:55,062 --> 01:02:56,272
You just press it?

1387
01:02:56,355 --> 01:02:57,565
I don't know.

1388
01:02:57,648 --> 01:02:58,983
There was something you pressed.

1389
01:03:00,109 --> 01:03:01,235
HE PRESSED THE STOP RECORDING BUTTON

1390
01:03:01,319 --> 01:03:02,737
<i>-Do you do this?</i>
<i>-It's this one.</i>

1391
01:03:02,820 --> 01:03:03,654
<i>Awesome.</i>

1392
01:03:03,738 --> 01:03:05,406
<i>-What do you think? Awesome, right?</i>
<i>-Yeah.</i>

1393
01:03:05,490 --> 01:03:07,533
<i>Hello, this person is…</i>

1394
01:03:07,617 --> 01:03:08,826
KYUNG-HO SUDDENLY BECOMES AN MC

1395
01:03:08,910 --> 01:03:10,536
<i>The person we invited today</i>

1396
01:03:10,620 --> 01:03:12,663
<i>is Ms. Lee Ye-rim.</i>

1397
01:03:12,747 --> 01:03:13,831
<i>-Yes.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

1398
01:03:13,915 --> 01:03:15,333
<i>What was your first impression of me?</i>

1399
01:03:15,416 --> 01:03:16,626
<i>-First impression?</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

1400
01:03:17,335 --> 01:03:19,086
<i>Do you want to hear</i>
<i>both the good and the bad?</i>

1401
01:03:19,170 --> 01:03:20,004
<i>Of course.</i>

1402
01:03:20,087 --> 01:03:21,422
<i>Honestly, the good part is that</i>

1403
01:03:22,423 --> 01:03:24,467
<i>-you were the prettiest.</i>
<i>-Okay.</i>

1404
01:03:25,051 --> 01:03:26,677
<i>And the bad part was</i>

1405
01:03:26,761 --> 01:03:28,262
<i>you looked like you had a temper</i>

1406
01:03:28,846 --> 01:03:29,972
<i>because you're the prettiest.</i>

1407
01:03:30,515 --> 01:03:31,974
<i>But what am I really like?</i>

1408
01:03:32,058 --> 01:03:32,975
<i>About what I expected.</i>

1409
01:03:35,770 --> 01:03:37,188
<i>What was your impression of me?</i>

1410
01:03:37,271 --> 01:03:39,941
<i>-You walked in looking super cocky.</i>
-Hello.

1411
01:03:41,067 --> 01:03:43,027
<i>-But you know…</i>
<i>-Yeah?</i>

1412
01:03:43,110 --> 01:03:44,612
<i>…there was a seat next to me,</i>

1413
01:03:45,363 --> 01:03:47,240
<i>so why did you sit next to Ga-yeon?</i>

1414
01:03:47,323 --> 01:03:49,408
<i>-I was feeling super awkward.</i>
<i>-I see.</i>

1415
01:03:49,492 --> 01:03:51,327
<i>So I just quickly sat down.</i>

1416
01:03:51,410 --> 01:03:54,622
<i>The seat in front of me</i>
<i>was the best option.</i>

1417
01:03:54,705 --> 01:03:55,998
<i>That's why I sat there.</i>

1418
01:03:57,124 --> 01:03:58,042
<i>Got it.</i>

1419
01:03:58,709 --> 01:04:02,088
ARRIVED AT THE LUGE BOARDING AREA

1420
01:04:02,797 --> 01:04:03,881
Which one do you want?

1421
01:04:03,965 --> 01:04:05,424
-I want the purple one.
-Okay.

1422
01:04:05,508 --> 01:04:06,467
Good. I'll go pink.

1423
01:04:06,968 --> 01:04:07,844
Come here.

1424
01:04:09,262 --> 01:04:10,221
The strap…

1425
01:04:13,516 --> 01:04:15,059
-You know…
-Yeah?

1426
01:04:15,142 --> 01:04:17,103
-Isn't Kyung-ho too much of a player?
-Why?

1427
01:04:19,021 --> 01:04:21,399
She may like that side of him.

1428
01:04:21,983 --> 01:04:23,734
Of course, a woman would like that.

1429
01:04:23,818 --> 01:04:24,819
Raise your chin.

1430
01:04:27,154 --> 01:04:28,239
Good?

1431
01:04:28,322 --> 01:04:29,949
-Yeah.
-Thanks.

1432
01:04:30,032 --> 01:04:31,868
-Go.
-Let's go.

1433
01:04:47,550 --> 01:04:48,926
Are you scared?

1434
01:04:49,010 --> 01:04:49,844
Nope.

1435
01:04:51,137 --> 01:04:52,096
Actually, I'm scared.

1436
01:04:52,179 --> 01:04:54,056
-Are you?
-It's a bit scary.

1437
01:04:55,057 --> 01:04:55,933
How cute.

1438
01:04:56,017 --> 01:04:58,144
Ye-rim looks cute like a kumquat.

1439
01:04:58,227 --> 01:05:00,271
She looks like she's on a motorcycle.

1440
01:05:06,235 --> 01:05:07,445
Why are you so slow?

1441
01:05:08,070 --> 01:05:09,572
How do you go fast?

1442
01:05:11,198 --> 01:05:12,575
Go slowly.

1443
01:05:17,246 --> 01:05:18,956
You look like a cartoon character.

1444
01:05:20,166 --> 01:05:21,876
You look really funny from behind.

1445
01:05:28,174 --> 01:05:29,425
How is it? Is it fun?

1446
01:05:29,508 --> 01:05:30,468
Yeah.

1447
01:05:30,551 --> 01:05:32,053
-It is fun.
-Are you having fun?

1448
01:05:33,596 --> 01:05:35,056
<i>She looked like she was having fun.</i>

1449
01:05:35,139 --> 01:05:36,849
<i>I could tell by her facial expression.</i>

1450
01:05:37,350 --> 01:05:38,809
She looked really cute

1451
01:05:39,393 --> 01:05:40,853
when she was riding it.

1452
01:05:51,697 --> 01:05:53,282
-That was fun.
-Did you have fun?

1453
01:05:53,366 --> 01:05:54,951
Yeah, it was so much fun.

1454
01:05:55,034 --> 01:05:57,078
-You were good.
-Nah.

1455
01:05:57,161 --> 01:05:59,038
TIME FOR A SOUVENIR PHOTO

1456
01:05:59,622 --> 01:06:01,499
-Can I take an annoying shot?
-Okay.

1457
01:06:03,084 --> 01:06:05,378
-Can I act like I'm riding really hard?
-Go on.

1458
01:06:07,588 --> 01:06:09,340
You look really cute.

1459
01:06:09,423 --> 01:06:10,841
Let's stop now.

1460
01:06:10,925 --> 01:06:12,718
You got embarrassed
when I complimented you.

1461
01:06:15,805 --> 01:06:18,516
-Can I take a weird shot too?
-Okay.

1462
01:06:19,433 --> 01:06:20,726
How should I pose?

1463
01:06:20,810 --> 01:06:23,980
Give me a more dynamic pose.

1464
01:06:25,106 --> 01:06:26,774
Okay. Good.

1465
01:06:29,860 --> 01:06:31,862
TAKING PHOTOS AT A PHOTO BOOTH

1466
01:06:31,946 --> 01:06:33,114
I feel so awkward.

1467
01:06:33,197 --> 01:06:35,950
<i>Three, two, one.</i>

1468
01:06:40,329 --> 01:06:41,205
Let's do a heart.

1469
01:06:41,956 --> 01:06:44,500
-How?
<i>-Three, two, one.</i>

1470
01:06:47,211 --> 01:06:48,921
-I covered your face.
-One more time, then.

1471
01:06:49,005 --> 01:06:49,922
Cover mine.

1472
01:06:52,967 --> 01:06:53,801
<i>One.</i>

1473
01:07:04,228 --> 01:07:05,396
They're looking good.

1474
01:07:05,896 --> 01:07:07,314
This is such eye candy.

1475
01:07:08,607 --> 01:07:09,608
Kiss.

1476
01:07:10,192 --> 01:07:11,027
One, two.

1477
01:07:13,112 --> 01:07:14,613
Want to add a caption?

1478
01:07:14,697 --> 01:07:15,698
A caption?

1479
01:07:15,781 --> 01:07:17,116
Don't look.

1480
01:07:17,199 --> 01:07:18,534
-Read it later.
-Okay.

1481
01:07:21,996 --> 01:07:24,248
AFTER THINKING FOR A MOMENT,
YE-RIM WRITES THE CAPTION

1482
01:07:30,629 --> 01:07:34,425
WHO WILL YOU GO ON A DATE WITH TOMORROW?

1483
01:07:37,094 --> 01:07:38,262
What?

1484
01:07:38,345 --> 01:07:40,347
It came out better than I thought.

1485
01:07:40,431 --> 01:07:41,432
-Here?
-Yeah.

1486
01:07:41,515 --> 01:07:43,642
I know. The photo came out really nicely.

1487
01:07:45,061 --> 01:07:47,271
<i>-You're standing close to that side.</i>
<i>-I am?</i>

1488
01:07:47,772 --> 01:07:48,981
CHAE-RIN AND DO-GEON
ARE OFF TO THEIR DATE

1489
01:07:49,065 --> 01:07:50,357
No, I'm not cold.

1490
01:07:52,151 --> 01:07:53,319
Thank you.

1491
01:07:55,988 --> 01:07:57,114
-I'm excited.
-Yeah.

1492
01:07:57,198 --> 01:07:59,158
-I really wanted to go out.
-Me too.

1493
01:07:59,658 --> 01:08:00,993
-Want me to do it?
-Yeah.

1494
01:08:02,453 --> 01:08:03,329
That's comfy.

1495
01:08:03,913 --> 01:08:06,082
My goodness.

1496
01:08:06,165 --> 01:08:07,291
They're so excited.

1497
01:08:07,374 --> 01:08:08,209
Kiss.

1498
01:08:08,292 --> 01:08:10,252
Did they have to do that?

1499
01:08:10,336 --> 01:08:12,171
-Just kiss now.
-Did they have to…

1500
01:08:12,755 --> 01:08:14,131
Why are you obsessed with kissing?

1501
01:08:14,215 --> 01:08:15,049
What's wrong?

1502
01:08:15,132 --> 01:08:16,509
Let's see some kissing now.

1503
01:08:16,592 --> 01:08:17,635
You need more excitement.

1504
01:08:17,718 --> 01:08:19,261
It's the fourth experiment.

1505
01:08:19,845 --> 01:08:21,514
The king can make them do it.

1506
01:08:23,474 --> 01:08:25,017
Make them do it!

1507
01:08:25,101 --> 01:08:26,268
-Make them do it!
-Do it!

1508
01:08:26,352 --> 01:08:27,478
If I were king,

1509
01:08:27,561 --> 01:08:29,814
I'd make two people
that are unrelated to me kiss.

1510
01:08:29,897 --> 01:08:32,108
"Hey, you two. Kiss. Do as the king says!"

1511
01:08:34,193 --> 01:08:35,528
-Want me to do it?
-Yeah.

1512
01:08:36,987 --> 01:08:37,863
That's comfy.

1513
01:08:40,908 --> 01:08:42,034
-You're weak.
-Just kidding.

1514
01:08:42,118 --> 01:08:43,786
You must not be an athlete.

1515
01:08:45,454 --> 01:08:47,998
The angle is a bit… Now it's good.

1516
01:08:48,082 --> 01:08:49,500
-Is this good?
-Yes.

1517
01:08:49,583 --> 01:08:50,793
-It's good.
-Okay.

1518
01:08:51,877 --> 01:08:52,962
I'm kidding.

1519
01:08:57,633 --> 01:09:00,261
-What was your first impression of me?
-My first impression?

1520
01:09:00,344 --> 01:09:04,473
Someone who looks different
from the others has arrived.

1521
01:09:05,224 --> 01:09:08,644
You looked very calm and honest.
You looked reserved.

1522
01:09:09,228 --> 01:09:10,437
Reserved?

1523
01:09:10,521 --> 01:09:12,857
-But the only seat left was next to me.
-Yeah.

1524
01:09:12,940 --> 01:09:14,525
How did it end up like that?

1525
01:09:14,608 --> 01:09:16,861
From what I can remember,

1526
01:09:16,944 --> 01:09:18,904
I felt like we clicked.

1527
01:09:18,988 --> 01:09:20,614
We sat next to each other
in the beginning,

1528
01:09:20,698 --> 01:09:22,575
-and we communicated well.
-Yeah.

1529
01:09:22,658 --> 01:09:23,617
That's what I thought.

1530
01:09:23,701 --> 01:09:25,077
-That's how you felt?
-Yeah.

1531
01:09:25,161 --> 01:09:26,954
What if you sat next to someone else?

1532
01:09:28,581 --> 01:09:30,374
I might not be sitting here.

1533
01:09:31,375 --> 01:09:32,376
Who knows?

1534
01:09:33,836 --> 01:09:35,004
I see.

1535
01:09:35,087 --> 01:09:37,548
-Are you usually playful?
-Me?

1536
01:09:37,631 --> 01:09:39,049
I can't say that I'm not playful.

1537
01:09:39,133 --> 01:09:40,176
I think you are.

1538
01:09:40,968 --> 01:09:42,219
When I date someone,

1539
01:09:42,303 --> 01:09:44,889
I tend to have a comfortable relationship.

1540
01:09:44,972 --> 01:09:46,599
-Like friends?
-Yeah.

1541
01:09:47,641 --> 01:09:48,893
What perfume do you use?

1542
01:09:48,976 --> 01:09:50,060
I brought it with me.

1543
01:09:56,400 --> 01:09:58,068
-Isn't it kind of gender-neutral?
-Yeah.

1544
01:09:58,903 --> 01:10:00,863
-It smells nice.
-Are you wearing any?

1545
01:10:02,448 --> 01:10:03,282
Smell right here.

1546
01:10:03,365 --> 01:10:04,783
The scent faded.

1547
01:10:05,451 --> 01:10:07,203
-I like it. It suits you.
-Really?

1548
01:10:07,286 --> 01:10:09,788
-Do you like scents like this?
-Kind of a unisex scent?

1549
01:10:10,623 --> 01:10:12,333
What kind of scent do you like in a woman?

1550
01:10:12,416 --> 01:10:13,417
The smell of shampoo.

1551
01:10:13,500 --> 01:10:14,919
-You like the smell of shampoo?
-Yeah.

1552
01:10:15,002 --> 01:10:16,712
The fresh-out-of-the-shower scent.

1553
01:10:17,796 --> 01:10:19,548
I really like that scent.

1554
01:10:21,133 --> 01:10:22,593
I wonder where we're going.

1555
01:10:25,471 --> 01:10:27,306
<i>What a coincidence</i>
<i>that we're making perfume.</i>

1556
01:10:27,890 --> 01:10:28,766
<i>Perfume.</i>

1557
01:10:28,849 --> 01:10:30,768
<i>Let's make perfume.</i>

1558
01:10:30,851 --> 01:10:34,688
You’re going to have a special experience
making a couple’s perfume.

1559
01:10:34,772 --> 01:10:39,068
Can you tell me
what kind of scents you like?

1560
01:10:39,151 --> 01:10:40,903
A freshly washed scent.

1561
01:10:40,986 --> 01:10:42,363
A soap scent.

1562
01:10:42,863 --> 01:10:43,948
Is that what you meant?

1563
01:10:44,031 --> 01:10:45,074
-A freshly washed scent.
-Okay.

1564
01:10:45,157 --> 01:10:47,660
Then, let's go ahead and make it.

1565
01:11:07,846 --> 01:11:09,056
-Hey.
-Do you like it?

1566
01:11:09,139 --> 01:11:10,683
-Is it okay?
-It smells familiar.

1567
01:11:10,766 --> 01:11:12,184
-What do you think?
-I like it.

1568
01:11:12,268 --> 01:11:15,896
<i>I used to think that</i>
<i>height doesn't matter.</i>

1569
01:11:16,397 --> 01:11:19,066
But since Do-geon is tall,

1570
01:11:19,149 --> 01:11:20,526
he seemed more attractive.

1571
01:11:20,609 --> 01:11:22,403
Especially his shoulders and his back.

1572
01:11:22,486 --> 01:11:23,904
He looked great.

1573
01:11:30,536 --> 01:11:31,578
This smells like shampoo.

1574
01:11:31,662 --> 01:11:33,789
Right? I like this one. I chose this.

1575
01:11:36,000 --> 01:11:37,251
I think you'll like this.

1576
01:11:38,836 --> 01:11:39,878
-Oh.
-Isn't it nice?

1577
01:11:39,962 --> 01:11:41,171
As soon as I smelled it…

1578
01:11:42,214 --> 01:11:44,758
I think we have similar taste.

1579
01:11:44,842 --> 01:11:46,093
-I know.
-Our taste in perfume.

1580
01:11:48,971 --> 01:11:50,639
What's up with your handwriting?

1581
01:11:50,723 --> 01:11:52,016
I didn't write that.

1582
01:11:52,099 --> 01:11:53,642
The lady wrote it earlier.

1583
01:11:54,226 --> 01:11:56,395
-Come on.
-I'm so sorry.

1584
01:11:56,478 --> 01:11:59,148
-Geez. You went too far.
-I was messing with him.

1585
01:11:59,231 --> 01:12:01,859
All right. Let's smell the fragrances now.

1586
01:12:01,942 --> 01:12:04,695
Cover it with your skin and let it settle.

1587
01:12:06,447 --> 01:12:07,781
You can set that down.

1588
01:12:12,328 --> 01:12:13,287
That smells so nice.

1589
01:12:13,370 --> 01:12:14,872
-Do you like it?
-Yeah, it's nice.

1590
01:12:19,168 --> 01:12:20,085
Is it too strong?

1591
01:12:21,503 --> 01:12:22,546
Here.

1592
01:12:22,629 --> 01:12:23,922
-Where?
-Here.

1593
01:12:25,924 --> 01:12:27,551
-This isn't bad.
-Isn't it nice?

1594
01:12:27,634 --> 01:12:29,678
It's better than this. Right here.

1595
01:12:33,265 --> 01:12:34,141
Where was yours?

1596
01:12:34,224 --> 01:12:35,267
It was this one.

1597
01:12:37,311 --> 01:12:39,104
I like this too.
Which one do you like more?

1598
01:12:39,188 --> 01:12:40,481
You put number four here, right?

1599
01:12:41,774 --> 01:12:43,734
Mine? Number four is here.

1600
01:12:46,278 --> 01:12:48,197
-This scent is really nice.
-Isn't it nice?

1601
01:12:49,782 --> 01:12:50,824
It has kind of

1602
01:12:51,450 --> 01:12:52,659
-a skin scent.
-Yeah.

1603
01:12:56,747 --> 01:12:57,998
This one's strong.

1604
01:12:58,082 --> 01:12:59,124
They're having a blast.

1605
01:13:00,376 --> 01:13:01,210
You know,

1606
01:13:01,293 --> 01:13:05,547
everyone has
their own natural skin scent, right?

1607
01:13:07,091 --> 01:13:08,300
Wait. What?

1608
01:13:08,384 --> 01:13:09,968
-No, just watch, Chan-mi.
-No.

1609
01:13:10,052 --> 01:13:11,387
-No, Joo-heon.
-No.

1610
01:13:11,470 --> 01:13:13,889
I don't want to break your concentration.

1611
01:13:13,972 --> 01:13:16,350
-It mixes with their skin scent.
-Yeah, it mixes with that.

1612
01:13:16,433 --> 01:13:18,519
-I was going to say that.
-His nose touched her.

1613
01:13:18,602 --> 01:13:20,104
I saw that too.

1614
01:13:22,147 --> 01:13:23,232
Can we pick the same one?

1615
01:13:23,315 --> 01:13:24,983
Yes, you can pick the same one.

1616
01:13:25,067 --> 01:13:26,151
Which one do you like more?

1617
01:13:28,654 --> 01:13:30,447
If you want to wear the same scent,

1618
01:13:30,531 --> 01:13:32,574
you can pick the same scent.

1619
01:13:33,700 --> 01:13:36,787
If you want the same scent
wherever you are, right?

1620
01:13:38,163 --> 01:13:39,456
We'll go with this one.

1621
01:13:39,540 --> 01:13:40,749
-Which one?
-We'll have the same scent.

1622
01:13:42,167 --> 01:13:43,877
You'll go with the same scent? Okay.

1623
01:13:43,961 --> 01:13:47,464
Take a look and pick the bottle you like.

1624
01:13:47,548 --> 01:13:48,757
I like this one the most.

1625
01:13:48,841 --> 01:13:50,342
Right? Me too.

1626
01:13:50,426 --> 01:13:51,635
Same scent and same bottle?

1627
01:13:52,886 --> 01:13:54,221
Please give us the same one.

1628
01:13:55,681 --> 01:13:58,809
You're going to add 2.7 grams
of fragrance oil.

1629
01:13:58,892 --> 01:14:01,103
Even if you add a lot at first,

1630
01:14:01,186 --> 01:14:02,855
it only reaches around 0.5 to 0.6 grams.

1631
01:14:02,938 --> 01:14:04,022
-Really?
-Yeah.

1632
01:14:04,106 --> 01:14:05,190
Go slowly.

1633
01:14:06,650 --> 01:14:08,235
-Wow.
-Wow.

1634
01:14:08,318 --> 01:14:09,194
I like it.

1635
01:14:09,278 --> 01:14:10,320
It looks so pretty.

1636
01:14:10,404 --> 01:14:11,864
I know. It's really pretty.

1637
01:14:11,947 --> 01:14:12,781
Amazing.

1638
01:14:20,497 --> 01:14:23,876
DO-GEON'S PERFUME FOR CHAE-RIN
CHAE-RIN'S PERFUME FOR DO-GEON

1639
01:14:27,504 --> 01:14:28,881
Smile a little.

1640
01:14:28,964 --> 01:14:30,132
Why aren't you smiling?

1641
01:14:39,975 --> 01:14:41,310
Just kiss.

1642
01:14:41,393 --> 01:14:42,644
Joo-heon!

1643
01:14:42,728 --> 01:14:44,521
Honestly, I feel the same way.

1644
01:14:44,605 --> 01:14:46,398
While they're taking the photo, they can…

1645
01:14:47,316 --> 01:14:49,067
Right? They just have to turn their heads.

1646
01:14:49,151 --> 01:14:51,236
-They're so close. Why not?
-Right?

1647
01:14:51,320 --> 01:14:52,404
They have to be a couple.

1648
01:14:52,488 --> 01:14:53,906
They're already dating.

1649
01:14:53,989 --> 01:14:55,699
This is what you call dating.

1650
01:14:56,492 --> 01:14:57,993
There isn't anything more to it.

1651
01:14:59,161 --> 01:15:00,787
Just hang on for a bit.

1652
01:15:01,538 --> 01:15:02,498
I like pretty women.

1653
01:15:02,581 --> 01:15:03,957
<i>I got a bit nervous.</i>

1654
01:15:04,041 --> 01:15:05,042
Did you want a compliment?

1655
01:15:05,125 --> 01:15:06,168
<i>I guess I was embarrassed?</i>

1656
01:15:06,251 --> 01:15:07,836
Honestly, I've never seen him as a man.

1657
01:15:07,920 --> 01:15:09,171
I may be different.

1658
01:15:09,254 --> 01:15:10,797
<i>I couldn't hide my expression.</i>

1659
01:15:10,881 --> 01:15:12,508
<i>I want to talk with someone else</i>

1660
01:15:12,591 --> 01:15:14,801
<i>since we don't have a lot of time.</i>

1661
01:15:14,885 --> 01:15:16,803
<i>Did I want to avoid this situation?</i>

1662
01:15:16,887 --> 01:15:17,763
Do you want to be king?

1663
01:15:17,846 --> 01:15:18,847
<i>King? It would be nice.</i>

1664
01:15:18,931 --> 01:15:20,516
<i>Let's plan it out and make it happen.</i>

1665
01:15:21,183 --> 01:15:22,851
One of the two has to win them over.

1666
01:15:22,935 --> 01:15:23,769
<i>Show him what I got?</i>

1667
01:15:23,852 --> 01:15:25,562
<i>I thought that was so mean.</i>

1668
01:15:25,646 --> 01:15:28,106
We can see the connections now.

1669
01:15:31,443 --> 01:15:32,402
<i>Isn't that no fun?</i>

1670
01:15:38,158 --> 01:15:40,160
Subtitle translation by: Ilyoung Kim

1671
01:15:40,244 --> 01:15:42,996
THE LOVE LAB
